Key Match Events: Australia beat South Africa by three wickets
David Miller scored a century (101 runs) for South Africa
Pat Cummins and Mitchell Starc took crucial wickets for Australia
Travis Head scored 62 runs for Australia
Post-Match Reflections: Rob Walter, South Africa's coach, disputed the notion of a choke
Pat Cummins and Mitchell Starc were hailed for their performances
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was South Africa's seventh exit at the semi-final stage across ODI and T20 World Cups
This was Australia's eighth men's 50-over World Cup final
Others: The match was played on a capricious, used pitch
The match was played at Eden Gardens
